         preservative system OR refrigeration OR short shelf (make weekly).
      Mitigations, best first:
        a) keep ribose + citrulline DRY; liquid-concentrate only the stable
           electrolyte/acid/dextrose fraction (loses single-bottle convenience).
        b) acidify hard (citric, pH <3.5), refrigerate, opaque bottle, 2-4 wk shelf.
        c) validated preservative + accelerated-stability (Tier 2) before any claim.
      NOTE: low pH suppresses Maillard (<pH4) but does NOT stop ribose browning
            or yeast/mold fully; bench stability data is required for a real shelf life.

